but your mother Comes every day.

243
00:21:58,208 --> 00:22:02,707
She keeps me company, you know.
And keeps everything in order.

244
00:22:02,708 --> 00:22:04,832
A little decorum is always necessary.

245
00:22:04,833 --> 00:22:06,916
That's how we were brought up.

246
00:22:06,917 --> 00:22:09,041
And with your wife, Luisa -- all fine?

247
00:22:09,042 --> 00:22:10,374
Yes. Luisa...

248
00:22:10,583 --> 00:22:14,082
You two together have been
my joy. Goodbye, son...

249
00:22:19,208 --> 00:22:22,666
What is this place?
Do you like it here?

250
00:22:23,833 --> 00:22:26,207
l haven't figured it out yet.

251
00:22:27,083 --> 00:22:31,207
But it's going much better.

252
00:22:32,292 --> 00:22:36,707
At first, you see, at first...

253
00:22:39,583 --> 00:22:43,707
Guido! I do my best.
What more Can l do?

254
00:22:54,667 --> 00:22:58,041
Poor Guido, you must be tired.
Shall we go home?

255
00:22:59,375 --> 00:23:01,957
l'm Luisa, your wife.
Don't you recognize me?

256
00:23:01,958 --> 00:23:03,916
What are you thinking about?

257
00:23:36,250 --> 00:23:37,707
- Hello.
- Hello.

258
00:23:55,250 --> 00:23:56,291
Good afternoon.

259
00:24:24,625 --> 00:24:27,416
Guido! In a few days,
l'll get you an introduction

260
00:24:27,417 --> 00:24:30,207
so you can get
all the advice you need.

261
00:24:30,208 --> 00:24:32,082
Nice mystical figure. Right?

262
00:24:32,083 --> 00:24:34,124
l brought you the three old men.

263
00:24:34,125 --> 00:24:36,207
One is a Russian,
another is a retired general...

264
00:24:36,208 --> 00:24:37,374
What old men?

265
00:24:37,375 --> 00:24:39,041
The ones for the role of the father.

266
00:24:39,042 --> 00:24:41,124
Cover me, Cesarino...

267
00:24:43,750 --> 00:24:45,374
Come here, buffoon.

268
00:24:45,958 --> 00:24:49,541
How are you?
So nice to see you, Super Tarzan!

269
00:24:50,042 --> 00:24:52,332
- I called you six times.
- Yes, yes l know.

270
00:24:52,333 --> 00:24:54,832
- It's about Claudia's script.
- So?

271
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:56,291
l thought about mailing it to you.

272
00:24:56,292 --> 00:24:58,332
ln fact, I've already mailed it.
- Really?

273
00:24:58,500 --> 00:25:01,457
You've still got your looks.
Why don't you go back to acting?

274
00:25:01,458 --> 00:25:03,916
l was up all night with
an idea for the spaceship.

275
00:25:03,917 --> 00:25:05,582
Why don't we make the upper story...

276
00:25:05,583 --> 00:25:09,749
ConocChia, don't take my arm!
l hate it! And wear a jaCket!

277
00:25:10,333 --> 00:25:12,582
Now l need to wear a jacket
to talk to you...

278
00:25:12,583 --> 00:25:14,624
How are you? How was your trip?

279
00:25:14,625 --> 00:25:16,582
Good. It's been an hour...

280
00:25:18,167 --> 00:25:22,166
What a blinding vision! Beautiful!

281
00:25:25,125 --> 00:25:26,791
- Really?
- Yes.

282
00:25:27,250 --> 00:25:29,249
You're always telling me
l'm 'bellissima'

283
00:25:29,250 --> 00:25:31,874
but you never tell me about my part.

284
00:25:31,875 --> 00:25:35,666
How was my screen test?
- Great, or you wouldn't be here.

285
00:25:35,667 --> 00:25:41,707
They told me I have to look
motherly and eat a lot of pasta.

286
00:25:44,208 --> 00:25:46,374
l should gain six pounds. Is this all?

287
00:25:46,375 --> 00:25:48,957
See? You already know
more than I do.

288
00:25:49,500 --> 00:25:53,166
You are the author.
You should be telling me something.

289
00:25:53,167 --> 00:25:55,624
- What should this lady do?
- What?

290
00:25:56,458 --> 00:25:57,541
Agostini!

291
00:25:59,375 --> 00:26:02,499
l don't want to bother you.
The hotel is grand,

292
00:26:02,667 --> 00:26:05,874
the whisky, excellent.
But I have three questions.

293
00:26:05,875 --> 00:26:09,624
Yes, yes, later. What is it?
Ah, yes, yes. Pardon me.

294
00:26:10,167 --> 00:26:11,499
Agostini, we should...

295
00:26:11,667 --> 00:26:14,749
l just didn't feel like talking to that guy.

296
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:17,624
Claudia is getting offers
from all over the world.

297
00:26:17,625 --> 00:26:20,624
l Can't keep her waiting.
Give her something.

298
00:26:20,625 --> 00:26:23,707
Do you have a script,
a few pages, an idea?

299
00:26:23,708 --> 00:26:26,666
Does Claudia realize that this
might be a great part?

300
00:26:26,667 --> 00:26:30,291
Perhaps the best she's ever
played? I'll explain...

301
00:26:38,458 --> 00:26:40,332
l'm telling you as a friend,
you're gonna lose her.

302
00:26:40,500 --> 00:26:43,541
- You want to see the old men or not?
- Are you crazy? We're ready...

303
00:26:43,542 --> 00:26:45,082
What?
- The old men.

304
00:26:45,083 --> 00:26:46,832
- Where are they?
- Here.

305
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:50,166
Signora Carla called. She doesn't
want to stay in that hotel.

306
00:26:50,167 --> 00:26:53,499
lt's ugly. She's right.
- What can I do? Bring her here?

307
00:26:53,500 --> 00:26:55,291
l'll Call the old men.

308
00:26:55,292 --> 00:26:58,499
Sorry, I wanted to introduce you
to my little wife.

309
00:26:58,500 --> 00:27:01,332
Thrilled.

310
00:27:01,875 --> 00:27:05,999
She writes too. She's a Columnist
for some ladies' magazines.

311
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:08,832
She's got a few questions for you.

312
00:27:08,833 --> 00:27:12,249
My readers go crazy for romance.

313
00:27:12,708 --> 00:27:16,749
Could you tell me something
about your love life?

314
00:27:16,750 --> 00:27:19,541
Here they are.
Say hello to the Dottore.

315
00:27:19,542 --> 00:27:23,582
Step down. You too, General.

316
00:27:25,667 --> 00:27:27,416
- How old are you?
- 70.

317
00:27:27,417 --> 00:27:29,082
- And you?
- 64.

318
00:27:30,667 --> 00:27:32,457
- And you?
- 68.

319
00:27:36,292 --> 00:27:38,166
They aren't old enough.

320
00:27:38,167 --> 00:27:39,999
What? This one
has one foot in the grave.

321
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:42,332
Next time l'll get three corpses.
You asked for a pathetiC type...

322
00:27:42,333 --> 00:27:46,124
This one makes you wanna Cry
the minute you see him.

323
00:27:51,708 --> 00:27:53,082
Hello, Commendatore.

324
00:27:56,750 --> 00:27:59,374
lf you kneel, what do l do?

325
00:27:59,375 --> 00:28:03,457
Get up or you'll hurt yourself.
How are you, little Guido?

326
00:28:03,625 --> 00:28:05,374
Hello, Commendatore.

327
00:28:05,375 --> 00:28:07,541
We took a helicopter.
This one screamed the whole way.

328
00:28:07,708 --> 00:28:08,499
Where's the swimming pool?

329
00:28:08,500 --> 00:28:10,749
We haven't even checked in. Shut up!

330
00:28:10,750 --> 00:28:12,041
Has the treatment helped?
- Yes.

331
00:28:12,042 --> 00:28:13,332
- Feeling better? Here.
- What is it?

332
00:28:13,333 --> 00:28:14,332
Just a token.

333
00:28:14,500 --> 00:28:16,416
- You're always giving me presents.
- It's just like mine.

334
00:28:16,417 --> 00:28:17,749
lt doesn't need winding.

335
00:28:17,750 --> 00:28:20,124
A watCh! A little watch, everyone!

336
00:28:22,875 --> 00:28:27,332
- So, are your ideas any clearer now?
- Yes, I really think so.

337
00:28:27,333 --> 00:28:29,249
We've got the Americans...

338
00:28:57,500 --> 00:29:00,499
l've seen her passport.
She's 52 years old?

339
00:29:00,500 --> 00:29:02,416
Ah, she's a little girl.

340
00:29:02,958 --> 00:29:04,457
Good evening, signora.

341
00:29:04,833 --> 00:29:07,582
And who are you, darling?

342
00:30:13,292 --> 00:30:16,749
Mr. Director, another little question...

343
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:26,332
He wants to know the relationship
between Catholicism and Marxism.

344
00:30:26,333 --> 00:30:27,707
Thank you, I got it.

345
00:30:27,917 --> 00:30:30,666
You want to know about
my political affiliation.

346
00:30:30,667 --> 00:30:34,916
As an honest man,
and all of you Italians are,

347
00:30:34,917 --> 00:30:37,999
you should be able to answer me.

348
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:42,249
ls Italy an essentially CatholiC country?

349
00:30:42,250 --> 00:30:42,999
Yes, it is!

350
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:45,457
You shut up and eat your ice-cream.

351
00:30:45,458 --> 00:30:48,249
lt's the estimate for the spaceship.

352
00:30:49,958 --> 00:30:53,332
l need to talk to you later,
face to face,

353
00:30:53,333 --> 00:30:57,707
l'm at the end of my rope.
This is a madhouse!

354
00:30:57,708 --> 00:31:02,416
fine, we'll disCuss it later.
What was that about your cholesterol?

355
00:31:22,250 --> 00:31:25,832
...only one great writer.
The early fitzgerald.

356
00:31:25,833 --> 00:31:30,457
Then his writing became an orgy
of pragmatism or brutal realism.

357
00:31:30,458 --> 00:31:33,791
What does Left or Right mean?

358
00:31:33,792 --> 00:31:36,582
You're such an optimist
to believe that in a world

359
00:31:36,750 --> 00:31:39,582
this confused and chaotic
there are people so lucid

360
00:31:39,583 --> 00:31:42,791
as to belong exclusively
to the Left or the Right.

361
00:31:42,792 --> 00:31:46,916
The Americans have this new
theory about cholesterol...

362
00:31:47,083 --> 00:31:49,999
- Is your ice-cream good?
- Very good.

363
00:31:54,417 --> 00:31:57,249
Could you say approximately
how many sCenes she'll be in?

364
00:31:57,250 --> 00:31:58,207
What?

365
00:31:58,208 --> 00:32:00,332
- How many scenes?
- Five.

366
00:32:02,917 --> 00:32:03,999
Only five.

367
00:32:04,250 --> 00:32:06,749
Maybe six, or even seven.

368
00:32:07,417 --> 00:32:08,457
Good evening.

369
00:32:09,292 --> 00:32:10,416
Hi, Guido.

370
00:32:11,667 --> 00:32:14,457
The Ambassador's got his eye on signora.

371
00:32:19,500 --> 00:32:20,541
So?

372
00:32:20,542 --> 00:32:22,749
- I thought you'd want to know.
- Good, now I know.

373
00:32:22,750 --> 00:32:25,957
- Do you want me to ask her to dance?
- Yes, ask her.

374
00:32:25,958 --> 00:32:28,624
Dear friends there's only one truth...

375
00:32:28,625 --> 00:32:33,541
But I am so anxious to know,
to understand my character.

376
00:32:33,542 --> 00:32:37,249
l need to coexist with my character
for a while before shooting...

377
00:32:37,250 --> 00:32:40,457
The lady says she needs
to know her character.

378
00:32:43,292 --> 00:32:47,374
l need to get inside her skin,
her ideas, or I'll fail.

379
00:32:47,875 --> 00:32:50,249
Hasn't the Maestro explained
the part yet?

380
00:32:50,417 --> 00:32:53,082
- No.
- I am sorry, dear lady.

381
00:32:53,083 --> 00:32:56,791
l don't have such information.
l'm only the producer.

382
00:32:57,042 --> 00:33:01,499
Guido, isn't it true that l know nothing?
- Right. Not a thing.

383
00:33:09,167 --> 00:33:11,041
And now three days of rest.

384
00:33:14,167 --> 00:33:18,957
They look like glass.
The first cherries of spring.

385
00:33:23,375 --> 00:33:24,916
Thanks. And for Guido?

386
00:33:32,458 --> 00:33:35,291
Mario Mezzabotta,
all 200 pounds of him.

387
00:33:35,833 --> 00:33:37,791
Shall we take a little walk?

388
00:33:41,625 --> 00:33:48,207
l know... Naturally,
you think I've lost it.

389
00:33:48,208 --> 00:33:49,166
Yes.

390
00:33:49,167 --> 00:33:52,291
- I'm 30 years her senior. So what?
- It's all right.

391
00:33:52,292 --> 00:33:57,457
l may be the fool, the old imbecile,
the one who foots the bill. So what?

392
00:33:57,792 --> 00:34:04,207
Could you create something important,
beautiful and real on a Commission?

393
00:34:04,208 --> 00:34:06,707
for instance, if the Pope asked you?

394
00:34:06,958 --> 00:34:09,832
Yes, yes. l'll think about it.
Excuse me.

395
00:34:11,667 --> 00:34:13,916
Listen, I'm not deluding myself.

396
00:34:14,250 --> 00:34:17,249
Maybe she's only with me
for the money.

397
00:34:18,292 --> 00:34:19,957
Actually, that's certainly it.

398
00:34:19,958 --> 00:34:23,416
But I've never felt closer
to anybody in my life.

399
00:34:23,958 --> 00:34:27,791
Just look at her.
She's pretty, Charming, intelligent.

400
00:34:28,167 --> 00:34:30,624
She has it all. Only for the money?

401
00:34:30,792 --> 00:34:33,999
But there are so many rich young men
around these days, loads of them.

402
00:34:34,000 --> 00:34:35,791
lt's clear. She cares for you.

403
00:34:35,792 --> 00:34:39,874
Right. And she hasn't tried
to pressure me.

404
00:34:40,292 --> 00:34:42,416
l made up my mind rationally.

405
00:34:43,083 --> 00:34:46,124
The poor thing has never
even mentioned my wife,

406
00:34:46,125 --> 00:34:48,374
my family, never a reproach.

407
00:34:48,667 --> 00:34:50,124
How did you meet her?

408
00:34:51,875 --> 00:34:55,124
ln London. She was in school
with my daughter.

409
00:34:56,167 --> 00:34:57,749
How many years have you
been married?

410
00:34:57,750 --> 00:34:59,541
Many. 31 .

411
00:34:59,958 --> 00:35:01,249
And your wife...

412
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:05,082
My wife took it really badly.
She hates her.

413
00:35:05,750 --> 00:35:08,874
While Gloria, poor thing,
is fond of her.

414
00:35:11,125 --> 00:35:13,457
So spell it out. I am a fool!

415
00:35:13,875 --> 00:35:16,416
There must be a shooting sChedule.
Dates.

416
00:35:16,417 --> 00:35:20,124
Otherwise we're off to Germany.
We have other offers.

417
00:35:20,125 --> 00:35:23,499
Will you be leaving me
in the dark 'til the end?

418
00:35:27,125 --> 00:35:29,166
You look like a little snail.

419
00:35:29,542 --> 00:35:32,916
- What is a little snail?
- Une petite escargot.

420
00:35:38,250 --> 00:35:40,916
Can you hear the voice
of the springs?

421
00:35:43,583 --> 00:35:46,541
The Romans used to call it
'Happy Waters.'

422
00:35:59,625 --> 00:36:03,249
Maya, let's entertain these bores.

423
00:36:04,208 --> 00:36:05,957
May l?

424
00:36:08,417 --> 00:36:11,291
Are you ready, Maya?
What am l holding?

425
00:36:12,625 --> 00:36:14,416
A velvet purse.

426
00:36:14,750 --> 00:36:17,332
- And inside?
- A white handkerchief.

427
00:36:18,458 --> 00:36:20,082
A red one.

428
00:36:21,458 --> 00:36:24,166
- No drugs, I hope.
- No, it's aspirin.

429
00:36:25,375 --> 00:36:27,957
- A purse.
- Is there any money in it?

430
00:36:27,958 --> 00:36:30,874
2,725 lire.

431
00:36:34,292 --> 00:36:36,791
And this lady here.
What is she thinking?

432
00:36:36,792 --> 00:36:38,624
No dirty thoughts, I hope.

433
00:36:38,625 --> 00:36:40,124
Just think about something.

434
00:36:40,125 --> 00:36:41,457
About what?

435
00:36:41,458 --> 00:36:43,957
Whatever you like.
Are you thinking?

436
00:36:44,375 --> 00:36:45,249
Yes.

437
00:36:45,250 --> 00:36:48,582
l'd like to live another 100 years.

438
00:36:50,958 --> 00:36:52,249
Best of luck!

439
00:36:53,750 --> 00:36:57,374
And what is in this pretty
lady's head?

440
00:36:57,375 --> 00:36:58,666
Let me be.

441
00:36:59,167 --> 00:37:01,082
May l think about someone?

442
00:37:01,083 --> 00:37:02,707
Yes. Go ahead, Lady!

443
00:37:03,125 --> 00:37:06,624
forget about it. l'm ashamed.

444
00:37:06,625 --> 00:37:08,291
What about?

445
00:37:08,542 --> 00:37:10,166
Can l really think of a person?

446
00:37:10,167 --> 00:37:12,874
l'd be afraid to have my thoughts read.

447
00:37:12,875 --> 00:37:14,916
Don't you worry darling,
no risk there.

448
00:37:14,917 --> 00:37:16,791
Would you like to leave? It's cold.

449
00:37:16,792 --> 00:37:19,957
A little kiss and a big slap.
ls that right?

450
00:37:22,500 --> 00:37:25,999
Ladies and gentlemen,
you're thinking, 'What a triCkster.'

451
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:28,749
Well, sorry to disappoint you,
but there's no trick.

452
00:37:28,750 --> 00:37:31,999
And it isn't just a coincidence.

453
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:34,332
lt's an exceptional example
of magnetic fields and telepathy.

454
00:37:34,500 --> 00:37:37,707
l transmit your thoughts to Mlle. Maya.

455
00:37:38,167 --> 00:37:41,499
You! Do you believe
you can hide your thoughts?

456
00:37:50,250 --> 00:37:53,457
Please, leave her alone.
Don't insist.

457
00:37:54,208 --> 00:37:55,582
Thoughts are sacred.

458
00:37:56,333 --> 00:37:58,291
See, it's all a game.

459
00:37:58,500 --> 00:37:59,874
Maya, are you ready?

460
00:38:00,833 --> 00:38:05,166
Just a moment, Could we know
what you gentlemen are thinking?

461
00:38:05,417 --> 00:38:06,582
You for instance.

462
00:38:06,583 --> 00:38:08,041
What are you thinking?

463
00:38:08,042 --> 00:38:11,416
What else? My director.
My cross and my delight.

464
00:38:11,667 --> 00:38:13,832
- How are you?
- Fine. And you?

465
00:38:14,792 --> 00:38:16,291
lt has been quite a while... years!

466
00:38:16,292 --> 00:38:18,249
Unfortunately yes, my dear.

467
00:38:18,917 --> 00:38:21,749
Just a moment. You're famous now.

468
00:38:21,750 --> 00:38:26,916
Cut it out.
Just tell me what's your trick?

469
00:38:26,917 --> 00:38:29,541
Well, it's partly a trick,
but part of it is real.

470
00:38:29,542 --> 00:38:32,457
l don't know how, but it happens.
- Can you transmit anything?

471
00:38:32,458 --> 00:38:35,041
Anything. Except for her to get lost.

472
00:38:35,833 --> 00:38:38,124
- Do you want to try?
- Yes. Wait.

473
00:38:38,125 --> 00:38:40,582
l bet now, with you, it won't work.

474
00:38:45,292 --> 00:38:50,124
l don't understand. I can't repeat...

475
00:39:16,167 --> 00:39:20,249
Asa... nisi... masa?
ls this right?

476
00:39:21,500 --> 00:39:23,499
- Right?
- Yes.

477
00:39:23,875 --> 00:39:25,916
But what does it mean?

478
00:39:32,500 --> 00:39:34,749
Guido, come here!
Where are you?

479
00:39:35,458 --> 00:39:37,291
Don't be spoiled! What a wonder!

480
00:39:37,292 --> 00:39:38,666
l don't want to take a bath,
l don't want to...

481
00:39:38,667 --> 00:39:40,332
Come here... Iet me catch you?

482
00:39:40,333 --> 00:39:41,707
l know what that rascal wants.

483
00:39:41,708 --> 00:39:43,374
He wants to be carried
by his sweetheart,

484
00:39:43,375 --> 00:39:45,041
doesn't he, the strapping lad.

485
00:39:45,042 --> 00:39:48,082
Come here. Come here.

486
00:39:48,083 --> 00:39:50,499
He never wants to take
the wine bath, the naughty boy.

