01:19:49,042 --> 01:19:51,207
What do I know? Ask him.

968
01:19:51,500 --> 01:19:55,582
Giancarlo wrote him
such a beautiful story about Martians.

969
01:19:55,792 --> 01:19:57,832
What is this amusement park for?

970
01:19:57,833 --> 01:19:59,999
You have no idea what
a job this was.

971
01:20:00,000 --> 01:20:03,374
No construCtion Company
wanted to take it on.

972
01:20:03,375 --> 01:20:05,124
lt rests entirely on sand.

973
01:20:05,125 --> 01:20:07,624
How much Concrete did it take?

974
01:20:08,083 --> 01:20:11,999
Tons! 400 tons.

975
01:20:12,000 --> 01:20:14,166
Commendatore, if you don't mind,

976
01:20:14,167 --> 01:20:17,374
l'll stop at the end of this
first flight. l have vertigo.

977
01:20:17,375 --> 01:20:20,124
for 80 million you could buy
at least ten apartments.

978
01:20:20,125 --> 01:20:22,791
lt's a pompous shaCk, just like him.

979
01:20:23,917 --> 01:20:26,582
The little sister-in-law is not
exactly tender with our director.

980
01:20:26,583 --> 01:20:28,291
Maybe she's in love with him.
- With him?

981
01:20:28,292 --> 01:20:31,249
l pray day and night
that l'll be spared a husband like him.

982
01:20:31,250 --> 01:20:32,916
What now? More climbing?

983
01:20:32,917 --> 01:20:34,791
l'd be glad to Carry you.

984
01:20:34,792 --> 01:20:39,374
When I think he made me spend
80 million on this structure.

985
01:20:39,375 --> 01:20:42,749
Wouldn't a well-crafted backdrop
have been better?

986
01:20:42,750 --> 01:20:45,666
A backdrop! That's out of
your grandfather's time.

987
01:20:45,667 --> 01:20:48,707
Besides, are they your millions,
ConocChia?

988
01:20:50,125 --> 01:20:54,249
Luisa, are you cold?
Take my jaCket.

989
01:20:54,250 --> 01:20:56,249
No, no. Thank you.

990
01:20:56,250 --> 01:20:58,957
Anyway, we're going
back to the hotel.

991
01:21:01,375 --> 01:21:02,957
ls something wrong?

992
01:21:02,958 --> 01:21:07,749
You've gotten sad all of a sudden.
Am l wrong?

993
01:21:08,708 --> 01:21:11,957
No. l'm not sad at all.

994
01:21:16,250 --> 01:21:18,624
The sequenCe starts with an image
of planet Earth

995
01:21:18,625 --> 01:21:21,874
completely wiped out
by a thermonuclear war...

996
01:21:22,083 --> 01:21:25,749
Guido seemed glad to see you,
really.

997
01:21:25,750 --> 01:21:30,124
...and the spaceship, our new Noah's Ark,
tries to escape, while the rest of humanity

998
01:21:30,125 --> 01:21:32,957
seeks refuge on another planet.

999
01:21:32,958 --> 01:21:36,707
More than 1 0,000 extras,
even 1 5,000, a tragic crowd.

1000
01:21:38,250 --> 01:21:41,457
We're really going to see all this
in your movie?

1001
01:21:41,625 --> 01:21:46,249
The prophet is raising his voice.
He's deCided to scare everybody.

1002
01:21:46,250 --> 01:21:50,207
Why not? Don't tell me you also love
movies where nothing happens?

1003
01:21:50,208 --> 01:21:53,416
ln my movie I have all
sorts of things happen.

1004
01:21:53,417 --> 01:21:57,166
l'm putting everything in.
Even a tap-dancing sailor.

1005
01:21:57,333 --> 01:21:58,916
Sailor, come here.

1006
01:21:58,917 --> 01:22:00,832
What did you learn in AmeriCa?

1007
01:22:01,000 --> 01:22:04,916
No, l don't want water.
Dance and I'll give you a part.

1008
01:22:04,917 --> 01:22:06,082
Dance.

1009
01:22:14,292 --> 01:22:16,499
What's up with you?
What's going on?

1010
01:22:16,500 --> 01:22:20,832
Rossella, cut the big sister tone.
lt puts me off right away.

1011
01:22:21,625 --> 01:22:24,124
Mr. Director, what part do l get?

1012
01:22:30,000 --> 01:22:32,832
What does Luisa think about me?
What does she want to do?

1013
01:22:32,833 --> 01:22:34,707
What's my part? My part?

1014
01:22:34,958 --> 01:22:35,999
Go away!

1015
01:22:37,250 --> 01:22:38,999
You know Luisa.
She doesn't say much.

1016
01:22:39,000 --> 01:22:41,249
Not even to me,
and l'm her best friend.

1017
01:22:41,250 --> 01:22:44,999
l really don't know. She's lost.

1018
01:22:45,000 --> 01:22:48,249
One day she says one thing,
another day, something else.

1019
01:22:48,250 --> 01:22:50,916
Unfortunately, I think the only
thing she'd like

1020
01:22:50,917 --> 01:22:53,041
is for you to be someone else.

1021
01:22:53,042 --> 01:22:54,249
Why?

1022
01:22:54,250 --> 01:22:56,582
lt's the mistake everyone makes.

1023
01:22:59,042 --> 01:23:03,541
But that kind little fellow,
is he in love with her?

1024
01:23:03,833 --> 01:23:07,957
You'd like that, so your conscience
won't gnaw at you anymore.

1025
01:23:07,958 --> 01:23:09,707
You're such a scoundrel.

1026
01:23:10,333 --> 01:23:15,416
Poor Enrico, he's so awkward.
Everybody's noticed.

1027
01:23:16,000 --> 01:23:19,291
He hangs around, listens to her,
keeps her company.

1028
01:23:19,292 --> 01:23:20,749
He's a great friend.

1029
01:23:24,917 --> 01:23:27,207
l thought my ideas were so Clear.

1030
01:23:28,125 --> 01:23:31,791
l wanted to make an honest film.
No lies whatsoever.

1031
01:23:32,667 --> 01:23:36,749
l thought I had something
so simple to say.

1032
01:23:38,125 --> 01:23:40,291
Something useful to everybody.

1033
01:23:40,292 --> 01:23:42,666
A film that could help to bury forever

1034
01:23:42,667 --> 01:23:46,082
all those dead things
we carry within ourselves.

1035
01:23:48,167 --> 01:23:52,749
lnstead, I'm the one without the courage
to bury anything at all.

1036
01:23:53,667 --> 01:23:59,041
And now I'm utterly confused.
This launch pad to deal with...

1037
01:24:02,167 --> 01:24:04,999
l wonder why things turned out
this way.

1038
01:24:06,708 --> 01:24:08,916
When did l go wrong?

1039
01:24:11,833 --> 01:24:13,999
l really have nothing to say...

1040
01:24:15,000 --> 01:24:17,374
but I want to say it all the same.

1041
01:24:19,208 --> 01:24:22,791
And your spirits,
why don't they come to my rescue?

1042
01:24:22,792 --> 01:24:25,416
You always said they had
plenty of messages for me.

1043
01:24:25,417 --> 01:24:27,082
Let them get to work!

1044
01:24:27,333 --> 01:24:30,999
l've already told you,
your attitude is wrong,

1045
01:24:31,000 --> 01:24:33,749
Your curiosity toward them is childish.

1046
01:24:34,167 --> 01:24:36,166
You want too many guarantees.

1047
01:24:36,167 --> 01:24:40,707
- Fine, but what do they say?
- Always the same thing. Even now.

1048
01:24:40,958 --> 01:24:44,457
They're very reasonable spirits.
They know you very well.

1049
01:24:44,458 --> 01:24:45,749
So?

1050
01:24:47,500 --> 01:24:51,207
They say you're free,
but you must learn to choose.

1051
01:24:51,833 --> 01:24:55,874
You don't have muCh time.
And you have to hurry.

1052
01:24:58,792 --> 01:25:02,999
Guido, are you coming up?
Yes or no?

1053
01:25:50,875 --> 01:25:52,124
Room 320, please.

1054
01:25:52,333 --> 01:25:53,457
Nobody's in.

1055
01:25:54,250 --> 01:25:55,416
fine, thanks.

1056
01:26:38,500 --> 01:26:40,207
Have you got a headache?

1057
01:26:40,708 --> 01:26:42,374
No, it's a tranquilizer.

1058
01:26:42,958 --> 01:26:44,541
Do you take them often?

1059
01:26:45,875 --> 01:26:47,832
Sometimes, to help me sleep.

1060
01:26:50,875 --> 01:26:52,541
What's worrying you now?

1061
01:27:17,417 --> 01:27:18,374
What?

1062
01:27:18,792 --> 01:27:21,582
Nothing.
lf you Could only see yourself.

1063
01:27:21,583 --> 01:27:23,041
Why are you laughing?

1064
01:27:23,250 --> 01:27:26,707
l don't think l Could ever betray you,
if only because l Couldn't bear

1065
01:27:26,875 --> 01:27:31,749
the ridiCulous effort
of having to hide and lie.

1066
01:27:32,292 --> 01:27:34,541
But obviously it's easy for you.

1067
01:27:34,958 --> 01:27:38,374
Listen Luisa.
l am very happy you're here,

1068
01:27:38,875 --> 01:27:42,124
but I am very tired and sleepy.

1069
01:27:46,542 --> 01:27:49,916
Sleep then. Good night.

1070
01:27:56,542 --> 01:28:00,082
l don't know what you think my
life is like, reducing it all

1071
01:28:00,083 --> 01:28:02,457
to the pettiness of somebody
stealing from the Cookie jar.

1072
01:28:02,458 --> 01:28:06,332
What do you know about my life?
What I hate and what I don't.

1073
01:28:06,333 --> 01:28:08,332
l only know what you show me.

1074
01:28:12,375 --> 01:28:13,999
What am l showing you?

1075
01:28:15,083 --> 01:28:17,207
Come on, tell me what you see.

1076
01:28:17,375 --> 01:28:20,499
You and yourjudgmental moralism.
What are you getting at?

1077
01:28:20,500 --> 01:28:24,249
Nothing. I know we've
been stagnating for years.

1078
01:28:25,000 --> 01:28:27,666
But it's you; you're the one
who always calls me back

1079
01:28:27,667 --> 01:28:30,124
and wants to start all over again.

1080
01:28:30,125 --> 01:28:32,916
Once and for all, I don't want
to restart anything.

1081
01:28:32,917 --> 01:28:34,374
But what do you want?

1082
01:28:34,750 --> 01:28:38,124
Why did you want me here?
What good am l to you?

1083
01:28:38,417 --> 01:28:42,374
What are you trying to get from me?
What is it you want?

1084
01:30:01,750 --> 01:30:06,082
Don't fret. I'd already spotted
her last night when I got in.

1085
01:30:14,833 --> 01:30:17,416
l've asked no questions,
so don't say a word.

1086
01:30:17,417 --> 01:30:21,666
Spare me the embarrassment
of having to listen to your lies.

1087
01:30:26,042 --> 01:30:28,124
She must have been born
in MarCh or April.

1088
01:30:28,125 --> 01:30:31,332
She's got all the characteristics
of an Aries. She's the Aries type.

1089
01:30:31,333 --> 01:30:33,499
l'll tell you what type she is.

1090
01:30:33,917 --> 01:30:37,457
Exactly the type most likely to make

1091
01:30:37,458 --> 01:30:42,082
a good companion for feeble,
spineless, confused men.

1092
01:30:43,208 --> 01:30:45,166
Luisa, I didn't know.

1093
01:30:45,750 --> 01:30:48,957
l'm seeing her for the first time,
like you.

1094
01:30:49,917 --> 01:30:52,749
Really, in a place like this,
where there are so many people,

1095
01:30:52,750 --> 01:30:55,832
it's no surprise to run into the poor thing.

1096
01:30:58,042 --> 01:31:01,291
So this is why you've been
tormenting me since last night.

1097
01:31:01,292 --> 01:31:02,957
You should have told me.

1098
01:31:05,500 --> 01:31:08,249
What annoys me most is
that people Could think

1099
01:31:08,250 --> 01:31:10,749
l'd go with somebody who
dresses that way.

1100
01:31:10,750 --> 01:31:12,124
Have you seen her clothes?

1101
01:31:12,125 --> 01:31:14,041
Listen, can't we go for a walk?

1102
01:31:14,042 --> 01:31:15,624
Let's not talk about this anymore.

1103
01:31:15,625 --> 01:31:19,082
lt's been over for three years.
finished. Enough.

1104
01:31:21,417 --> 01:31:25,332
He drives me crazy.
He pretends he's telling the truth.

1105
01:31:25,333 --> 01:31:29,041
He acts honest.
As if he's the one who's right.

1106
01:31:30,625 --> 01:31:32,624
How can you live this way?

1107
01:31:34,958 --> 01:31:36,499
lt's not right living this way,

1108
01:31:36,500 --> 01:31:38,957
not letting others know
what's true and what's false.

1109
01:31:38,958 --> 01:31:41,749
ls it possible that for you
it's all the same? How?

1110
01:31:41,750 --> 01:31:45,041
You're right. I know, I'm boring.

1111
01:31:46,417 --> 01:31:51,082
How sad having to play
the bourgeois wife who doesn't understand.

1112
01:31:51,083 --> 01:31:53,166
You tell me, what should I do.

1113
01:31:53,375 --> 01:31:55,249
l really can't laugh about it
the way you do.

1114
01:31:55,250 --> 01:31:57,249
No darling, I'm not laughing.

1115
01:31:59,708 --> 01:32:02,249
What do you tell her?

1116
01:32:07,333 --> 01:32:10,791
What disgusts me the most is that
you've mixed her up in our life.

1117
01:32:10,792 --> 01:32:13,457
She knows everything
about you and me.

1118
01:32:14,500 --> 01:32:17,707
That whore. Cow!

1119
01:32:20,917 --> 01:32:23,457
You're a real pain, you know.

1120
01:32:31,417 --> 01:32:32,749
And yet...

1121
01:32:56,083 --> 01:32:58,707
Signora Carla, you sing so well.

1122
01:32:58,917 --> 01:33:00,624
No, l'm just an amateur.

1123
01:33:00,792 --> 01:33:02,457
And how pretty you look.

1124
01:33:03,417 --> 01:33:06,916
l've wanted to meet you for so long.
- And I, you.

1125
01:33:13,208 --> 01:33:14,791
You're so stylish.

1126
01:33:14,792 --> 01:33:18,999
No, you're the stylish one.
Me, frankly, I'm a bit trashy.

1127
01:33:19,000 --> 01:33:20,749
What are you talking about?
This is so refined.

1128
01:33:20,750 --> 01:33:21,666
Do you like it?

1129
01:33:21,667 --> 01:33:23,791
lt's a little outfit I found in Vogue.
- Really?

1130
01:33:23,792 --> 01:33:25,832
lf you only knew how long
it took me to find it.

1131
01:33:25,833 --> 01:33:28,874
But you know,
when Carla wants something...

1132
01:33:42,167 --> 01:33:44,582
Here he comes!

1133
01:33:44,583 --> 01:33:47,291
Guido's here.

1134
01:33:48,250 --> 01:33:49,957
Good evening, women.

1135
01:33:49,958 --> 01:33:52,207
Close the door, there's a storm.

1136
01:33:53,458 --> 01:33:55,207
How are you? Well?

1137
01:33:55,208 --> 01:33:57,332
Every gift comes with its nametag.

1138
01:33:57,333 --> 01:34:00,082
Don't get mixed up.
This is Caterina's.

1139
01:34:00,750 --> 01:34:02,207
He's a darling!

1140
01:34:02,500 --> 01:34:04,832
And this one is for my darling sister-in-law,

1141
01:34:04,833 --> 01:34:07,832
because she's finally understood
how things should be.

1142
01:34:08,000 --> 01:34:09,624
We'll draw your bath right away.

1143
01:34:09,625 --> 01:34:11,541
Gloria, this is you-know-what.

1144
01:34:11,542 --> 01:34:14,499
Thanks. I need to talk to you, Guido.

1145
01:34:15,292 --> 01:34:17,624
l know what she wants to tell you.

1146
01:34:17,625 --> 01:34:20,374
Now we'll have to send her away
because she's acting jealous.

1147
01:34:20,375 --> 01:34:22,791
What were you doing upstairs?

1148
01:34:22,792 --> 01:34:26,749
l went to see those poor things.
They'd always be alone, if not for me.

1149
01:34:26,750 --> 01:34:30,291
The role doesn't suit her.
She's only a common bourgeoise.

1150
01:34:30,292 --> 01:34:31,582
She has no Class.

1151
01:34:31,583 --> 01:34:34,332
Leave him alone now.
He's got to take his bath.

1152
01:34:34,500 --> 01:34:37,624
Oh Guido, this is splendid,
l've always wanted one like it.

1153
01:34:37,625 --> 01:34:40,124
Hurry, Carla, Hedy!
Get the buckets.

1154
01:34:43,167 --> 01:34:45,249
Guido, my husband wrote.

1155
01:34:45,250 --> 01:34:48,291
He wants me home for New Year's,
just for a day, do you mind?

1156
01:34:48,292 --> 01:34:51,499
lf you do, l'll tell him I can't.
- I think that will be fine.

1157
01:34:51,500 --> 01:34:52,791
Come on, Carlotta!

1158
01:34:56,792 --> 01:34:59,666
- Who's that little black girl?
- A surprise from us.

1159
01:34:59,667 --> 01:35:02,624
She's from Hawaii,
don't you remember her?

1160
01:35:03,375 --> 01:35:05,916
You told us about her
so many times.

1161
01:35:11,083 --> 01:35:13,541
Thank you, Luisa. You're so kind.

1162
01:35:13,542 --> 01:35:15,707
Such a delicate little present.

1163
01:35:22,917 --> 01:35:24,332
That tiara is mine.

1164
01:35:24,333 --> 01:35:27,457
Yes, l know.
l'll give it back to you later.

1165
01:35:28,625 --> 01:35:29,832
Oh, darling!

1166
01:35:30,583 --> 01:35:32,749
What a thrill to find you here.

1167
01:35:33,083 --> 01:35:34,916
- How are you?
- Fine.

1168
01:35:35,417 --> 01:35:39,457
But do tell me, who are you?

1169
01:35:39,458 --> 01:35:42,749
The name doesn't matter.
l'm happy to be here.

1170
01:35:42,750 --> 01:35:45,457
Don't ask me any questions.
- Can I stay?

1171
01:35:45,458 --> 01:35:49,666
Of course, you pretty thing.
l'm busy now.

1172
01:35:49,667 --> 01:35:51,249
But later?

1173
01:35:54,083 --> 01:35:56,499
Rossella?
What are you doing here?

1174
01:35:56,500 --> 01:35:58,999
Playing PinoCchio's wise cricket.
Do you mind?

1175
01:35:59,000 --> 01:36:00,332
No. But why are you laughing?

1176
01:36:00,333 --> 01:36:03,249
lt's nothing. l just want to see
how you get out of this one.

1177
01:36:03,250 --> 01:36:06,707
You've finally got your harem,
King Solomon!

1178
01:36:06,875 --> 01:36:09,041
- It was high time.
- Sure was.

1179
01:36:13,125 --> 01:36:14,749
Lower me down.

1180
01:36:15,125 --> 01:36:18,291
Aren't you a little sCared?

1181
01:36:18,500 --> 01:36:20,874
Of what? Everything is going great.

1182
01:36:20,875 --> 01:36:22,457
Can l stay too? l'm having suCh fun.

1183
01:36:22,458 --> 01:36:24,791
l don't want anything.
l'll just watch you.

1184
01:36:24,792 --> 01:36:26,999
We have rules that must be
respeCted. Do you know that?

1185
01:36:27,000 --> 01:36:28,082
Come, help me.

1186
01:36:30,708 --> 01:36:34,999
lt's a two piece suit with a busby
in ostriCh feathers. Do you like it?

1187
01:36:35,000 --> 01:36:37,457
Hi Hedy, it's beautiful.

1188
01:36:38,708 --> 01:36:40,291
So, what are the rules?

1189
01:36:40,625 --> 01:36:43,624
l don't know. He promised me
a part in his movie and said

1190
01:36:43,625 --> 01:36:45,916
l'd have to change dresses a lot.

1191
01:36:50,917 --> 01:36:53,541
Girls, that's enough. Get me out.

1192
01:36:55,458 --> 01:36:58,207
- Gloria, the talcum powder.
- Ah, yes.

1193
01:37:00,792 --> 01:37:03,207
Guido, do you know she prepared
something just the way you like it?

1194
01:37:03,208 --> 01:37:05,541
- Really?
- A cake.

1195
01:37:05,542 --> 01:37:08,166
- Are you happy, girls?
- Of course!

1196
01:37:08,167 --> 01:37:09,916
lsn't this just what
you always wanted?

1197
01:37:09,917 --> 01:37:13,166
Certainly! lsn't he the best
kid in the world?

1198
01:37:13,542 --> 01:37:15,541
Nadine, hurry up with the powder!

1199
01:37:15,708 --> 01:37:19,166
Oh Nadine, what was it you used
to say in Copenhagen?

1200
01:37:19,167 --> 01:37:21,624
We're delighted to invite
our passengers

1201
01:37:21,625 --> 01:37:24,916
to spend the night in Copenhagen
due to a problem with the motor.

1202
01:37:24,917 --> 01:37:27,666
