02:09:04,542 --> 02:09:08,999
Of any artist truly worth the name
we should ask nothing

1676
02:09:09,000 --> 02:09:12,249
except this act of faith: to learn silence.

1677
02:09:12,708 --> 02:09:15,416
Do you remember Mallarme's
homage to the white page?

1678
02:09:15,417 --> 02:09:16,791
And Rimbaud...
- Guido, wait!

1679
02:09:16,792 --> 02:09:19,499
...a poet, my friend, not a movie director.
What was his finest poetry?

1680
02:09:19,667 --> 02:09:21,707
We're ready to begin.

1681
02:09:21,708 --> 02:09:25,291
His refusal to continue writing
and his departure for Africa.

1682
02:09:25,292 --> 02:09:26,666
Congratulations.

1683
02:09:26,667 --> 02:09:30,832
lf we Can't have everything,
true perfection is nothingness.

1684
02:09:30,833 --> 02:09:35,791
forgive me for quoting all the time.
But we critiCs... do what we Can.

1685
02:09:36,458 --> 02:09:40,624
Our true mission is... sweeping away
the thousands of miscarriages

1686
02:09:40,625 --> 02:09:45,041
that everyday... obscenely...
try to Come to the light.

1687
02:09:45,750 --> 02:09:50,166
And you would actually dare leave
behind you a whole film,

1688
02:09:50,750 --> 02:09:54,624
like a Cripple who leaves behind
his crooked footprint.

1689
02:09:55,042 --> 02:09:57,457
Such a monstrous presumption
to think

1690
02:09:57,458 --> 02:10:02,416
that others Could benefit from the
squalid catalogue of your mistakes!

1691
02:10:02,708 --> 02:10:05,457
And how do you benefit
from stringing together

1692
02:10:05,458 --> 02:10:06,916
the tattered pieces of your life?

1693
02:10:06,917 --> 02:10:09,791
Your vague memories, the faces of people

1694
02:10:09,792 --> 02:10:12,249
that you were never able to love...

1695
02:10:20,667 --> 02:10:23,249
What is this sudden happiness
that makes me tremble,

1696
02:10:23,250 --> 02:10:24,999
giving me strength, life?

1697
02:10:26,500 --> 02:10:28,582
forgive me, sweet creatures.

1698
02:10:28,583 --> 02:10:31,041
l hadn't understood. I didn't know.

1699
02:10:31,333 --> 02:10:34,207
lt's so natural accepting you,
loving you.

1700
02:10:34,208 --> 02:10:35,791
And so simple.

1701
02:10:36,417 --> 02:10:39,332
Luisa, I feel I've been freed.

1702
02:10:39,875 --> 02:10:42,166
Everything seems so good,
so meaningful.

1703
02:10:42,167 --> 02:10:43,457
Everything is true.

1704
02:10:43,833 --> 02:10:45,749
l wish I could explain.

1705
02:10:46,458 --> 02:10:48,291
But I don't know how to.

1706
02:10:49,208 --> 02:10:53,082
So. Everything is Confused again,
as it was before.

1707
02:10:53,250 --> 02:10:54,041
The lights!

1708
02:10:54,208 --> 02:10:55,832
But this confusion is... me.

1709
02:10:55,833 --> 02:10:58,832
Not as I'd like to be, but as I am.

1710
02:10:59,333 --> 02:11:03,332
l'm not afraid anymore
of telling the truth,

1711
02:11:03,333 --> 02:11:07,582
of the things I don't know,
what l'm looking for and haven't found.

1712
02:11:07,583 --> 02:11:09,166
This is the only way I can feel alive

1713
02:11:09,167 --> 02:11:12,582
and l Can look into your faithful
eyes without shame.

1714
02:11:12,583 --> 02:11:14,207
Life is a celebration.

1715
02:11:14,208 --> 02:11:15,832
Let's live it together!

1716
02:11:17,000 --> 02:11:19,999
This is all l Can say Luisa,
to you or the others.

1717
02:11:20,000 --> 02:11:22,416
Accept me for what I am,
if you want me.

1718
02:11:22,417 --> 02:11:25,999
lt's the only way we might be able
to find each other.

1719
02:11:26,000 --> 02:11:28,666
l don't know if what
you said to me is right.

1720
02:11:28,667 --> 02:11:31,666
But I can try if you help me.

1721
02:12:31,500 --> 02:12:34,457
Just a minute.
l'll give you the go-ahead.

1722
02:12:44,250 --> 02:12:47,166
Now. Go to the curtain.

1723
02:12:56,833 --> 02:12:57,832
Draw it.

1724
02:12:59,875 --> 02:13:01,999
Everyone come down.

1725
02:13:02,000 --> 02:13:04,457
Talk to each other.

1726
02:13:55,875 --> 02:13:56,916
Mother.

1727
02:14:02,583 --> 02:14:06,041
Sgulp! I did understand what
you wanted to say, you know.

1728
02:14:06,042 --> 02:14:08,082
That you can't do without us.

1729
02:14:08,375 --> 02:14:12,374
At what time will you call me tomorrow?
- Fine, fine. Now join the line!

1730
02:14:12,375 --> 02:14:13,332
MauriCe!

1731
02:14:17,542 --> 02:14:21,666
Come, quickly!
Stop fooling around.

1732
02:14:21,917 --> 02:14:26,582
Everybody hold hands!
Spread out! All together.

1733
02:14:29,250 --> 02:14:30,207
Maestro!

1734
02:14:30,833 --> 02:14:33,082
Let's all hold hands!

